  "prompt": "Who discovered chloroplast?",
  "response": "The discovery of chloroplasts is often attributed to the work of several scientists in the 19th century. One primary figure is Andreas Franz Wilhelm Schimper, a German botanist. In the late 1880s, Schimper provided detailed descriptions of chloroplasts and was among the first to suggest their role in photosynthesis. Additionally, while earlier observations of plant cells and their green structures were made by others like Antonie van Leeuwenhoek and Hugo von Mohl, Schimper's work was critical in advancing the understanding of chloroplasts as distinct organelles involved in the process of photosynthesis.",
